755 for directories, 644 for files; executables 755.

```bash
find /path/to/dir -type d -exec stat -c '%a %n' {} \;
find /path/to/dir -type f -exec stat -c '%a %n' {} \;
```

```bash
find /path/to/dir -type d -exec chmod 755 {} \;
find /path/to/dir -type f -exec chmod 644 {} \;
find /path/to/dir -type f -name '*.sh' -exec chmod 755 {} \;
```

If ownership is wrong:

```bash
chown -R user:group /path/to/dir
```
